quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  58,12,"O ye who believe! when ye go to confer in private with the Apostle, give alms before such conference. Better will this be for you, and more pure. But if ye have not the means, then truly God is Lenient, Merciful"
  58,13,"Do ye hesitate to give alms previously to your private conference? Then if ye do it not (and God will excuse it in you), at least observe prayer, and pay the stated impost, and obey God and His Apostle: for God is cognisant of your actions"
  58,14,"Hast thou not remarked those who make friends of that people with whom God is angered? They are neither of your party nor of theirs; and they swear to a lie, knowing it to be such"
  58,15,"God hath got ready for them a severe torment: for, evil is that they do"
  58,16,"They make a cloak of their faith, and turn others aside from the way of God: wherefore a shameful torment awaiteth them"
  58,17,"Not at all shall their wealth or their children avail them aught against God. Companions shall they be of the fire: they shall abide therein for ever"
  58,18,"On the day when God shall raise them all, they will swear to Him as they now swear to you, deeming that it will avail them. Are they not - yes they - the liars"
  58,19,"Satan hath gotten mastery over them, and made them forget the remembrance of God. These are Satan's party. What! shall not verily the party of Satan be for ever lost"
  58,20,"Verily, they who oppose God and His Apostle shall be among the most vile"
  58,21,"God hath written this decree: \"I will surely prevail, and my Apostles also.\" Truly God is Strong, Mighty"